The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, specifically the Feedback Vertex Set problem in tournaments. This problem is related to directed graphs and cycles, which are common topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new partitioning theorem for undirected graphs, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses algorithmic improvements for the Feedback Vertex Set problem, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
